            "content": {
                "raw": "Yes, always a scalar.  It is the size of the image along the longest axis in the final plot.  Since the aspect ratio of PlotWindow plots are controlled by the `width` keyword we can't also accept a tuple for `figure_size`.  We could for `PhasePlot` but no one has implemented that.\n\nDo you want me to add an error if someone passes in a tuple?",
                "html": "<p>Yes, always a scalar.  It is the size of the image along the longest axis in the final plot.  Since the aspect ratio of PlotWindow plots are controlled by the <code>width</code> keyword we can't also accept a tuple for <code>figure_size</code>.  We could for <code>PhasePlot</code> but no one has implemented that.</p>\n<p>Do you want me to add an error if someone passes in a tuple?</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
