            "content": {
                "raw": "I've been meaning to change this default for a while.  The idea is that the entire plot should fit inside of an IPython notebook cell with a little bit of room to spare on a laptop display.\n\nLike I mention in the PR description, I'm ok with reverting it if people disagree.  Try checking out the tip of this PR and make some test plots.  Even better, use the test notebook I link to in the PR description, which lets you interactively control the figure size.",
                "html": "<p>I've been meaning to change this default for a while.  The idea is that the entire plot should fit inside of an IPython notebook cell with a little bit of room to spare on a laptop display.</p>\n<p>Like I mention in the PR description, I'm ok with reverting it if people disagree.  Try checking out the tip of this PR and make some test plots.  Even better, use the test notebook I link to in the PR description, which lets you interactively control the figure size.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
