            "content": {
                "raw": "Well, to be honest, my preference is not to change the plot size in reference to the notebook.  I don't want to say no, but I think we should not (yet) be optimizing for that mode of operation.  Is there a way we could modify our `__repr_html__` to scale the image to fit in a cell?  Additionally, on different monitors and displays we will have different sizes that can be displayed.",
                "html": "<p>Well, to be honest, my preference is not to change the plot size in reference to the notebook.  I don't want to say no, but I think we should not (yet) be optimizing for that mode of operation.  Is there a way we could modify our <code>__repr_html__</code> to scale the image to fit in a cell?  Additionally, on different monitors and displays we will have different sizes that can be displayed.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
