            "content": {
                "raw": "I don't think it's a good idea to scale down the plots like that since it will make the text harder to read.\n\nI think 10 inches (or even 8) is awkwardly huge, even using an image viewer on a desktop display - completely ignoring the notebook use case.  If you open these links in new tabs you can compare see how big our current default is.  You may need to zoom in, as most browsers will automatically scale images that don't fit inside the display.\n\n[10 inches](https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/437117810-10_inches_Slice_z_density.png)\n\n[8 inches](https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/2385219573-8_inches_Slice_z_density.png)\n\n[6 inches](https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/3789403601-6_inches_Slice_z_density.png)\n\nAlso, I think it is worth thinking about the usability experience in the notebook as we design our code.  I use yt inside of a notebook more often than not and I would hope that we would at least give it some thought and try to fix real usability issues.  If this means changing a default value somewhere in the code, I don't think that's a huge stretch.",
                "html": "<p>I don't think it's a good idea to scale down the plots like that since it will make the text harder to read.</p>\n<p>I think 10 inches (or even 8) is awkwardly huge, even using an image viewer on a desktop display - completely ignoring the notebook use case.  If you open these links in new tabs you can compare see how big our current default is.  You may need to zoom in, as most browsers will automatically scale images that don't fit inside the display.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/437117810-10_inches_Slice_z_density.png\">10 inches</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/2385219573-8_inches_Slice_z_density.png\">8 inches</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/repo/BXbAb/images/3789403601-6_inches_Slice_z_density.png\">6 inches</a></p>\n<p>Also, I think it is worth thinking about the usability experience in the notebook as we design our code.  I use yt inside of a notebook more often than not and I would hope that we would at least give it some thought and try to fix real usability issues.  If this means changing a default value somewhere in the code, I don't think that's a huge stretch.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
